query.result:
76 As if they are ruminating slowly 77 the goats, standing swift and bold 78 over the peaks ahead that are prancing,
79 silent in the shade, while the sun burns, 80 watched by the shepherd, who on the staff 81 leaning he is and serves them for rest;
82 and like the mandrill that lives outside, 83 along his little hill he quietly spends the night, 84 watching that the beast does not scatter it;
