130 Tratto t’ho qui con ingegno e con arte;
131 lo tuo piacere omai prendi per duce;
132 fuor se’ de l’erte vie, fuor se’ de l’arte.

query.result:
130 I have drawn you here with ingenuity and with art;  
131 now take your pleasure as a guide;  
132 you are beyond the steep ways, you are beyond the art.

133 See the sun that on your forehead shines;  
134 see the little herbs, the flowers and the little shrubs  
135 that here the earth alone from itself produces.
